<h2 id="section-top">Speech and language services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=633">Chesterfield Royal Hospital NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Chesterfield Royal Hospital<br/>01246 512080</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent5bccb0db42cb4c06a70222dd22c4079e">
</div>
<p><strong>Speech &amp; Language Therapy</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>Speech and Language Therapy for children and adults is available at Chesterfield Royal NHS Foundation Trust.</p>
<p>The children’s services for North Derbyshire are based in the Women’s and Children’s Directorate and can be contacted on 01246 514621.</p>
<p>The services for Adults are based in the Central Services Directorate with other allied health professions.</p>
<p> In and outpatient services are provided. We provide specialist services in the management of acquired speech, language, voice and swallowing difficulties associated with stroke and other neurological difficulties, head and neck cancers, voice disorders and dysfluency (stammering).</p>
<p>The department is based in Outpatient Suite 5 and can be contacted on (01246) 512080, Monday to Friday 8.30 to 5.15 pm.</p></div>
</div>
